 | A-055 | Authoritative loan-limit concurrency tests run only through `sfpcl_credit.config.postgres_test_settings`; the default SQLite suite explicitly skips them because SQLite does not implement `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`. PostgreSQL connection values are environment supplied, with conventional local defaults. | Codebase-design §26.3 requires concurrency tests for financial modules, while the existing local settings are SQLite-only and the source requires PostgreSQL for production. Treating SQLite success as row-lock evidence would be false assurance. | `docs/source/codebase-design.md` §22.3/§26.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §34; `docs/slices/006D2C-loan-limit-concurrency-and-boundary-regression.md`; `docs/working/DEPENDENCY_POLICY.md` | 006D2C and every future change to loan-limit locking | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Independent validation must install pinned `psycopg[binary]`, provision PostgreSQL, and run `manage.py test sfpcl_credit.tests.test_credit_modules.LoanLimitConcurrencyTests --settings=sfpcl_credit.config.postgres_test_settings -v 2`; a SQLite skip is never acceptance evidence. |
 | A-056 | Ambiguous legacy appraisal repair uses `POST /api/v1/appraisal-notes/{id}/revalidate-prerequisites/` with an empty body, appraisal-update plus risk-management permission, object scope, and draft-only state. | ADR-0003 and 006E2 require explicit authorised revalidation but the source API document does not name its path/body. A dedicated action endpoint matches API §3, avoids overloading PATCH, and changes only frozen prerequisite facts. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3/§24; `docs/adr/ADR-0003-freeze-appraisal-prerequisite-projections.md`; `docs/slices/006E2-appraisal-source-contract-and-snapshot-hardening.md` | 006E2 and later appraisal review/sanction slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance names a different repair action, version/alias the route while retaining draft-only authorisation, immutable caller-authored facts, and metadata-only evidence. |
